  "prompt": "Has anyone received any call from companies, cut-off of which has been been cleared in LinkedIn Placements Test?",
  "response": "It\u2019s common for candidates who have cleared placement tests or assessments on platforms like LinkedIn to receive calls or follow-up communications from companies. However, the timing and nature of these communications can vary based on the company's recruitment process. \n\nIf you are inquiring about receiving calls specifically from companies associated with LinkedIn placements, it may depend on a variety of factors, including:\n\n1. **Individual Profiles**: Companies often look for specific skills that align with their needs, so not all candidates will be contacted.\n\n2. **Job Market Demand**: The demand for certain skills in the job market can influence how quickly companies reach out to candidates.\n\n3. **Follow-up Actions**: Sometimes, candidates may need to take further steps to express interest or apply to open positions.\n\nConsider networking within LinkedIn and looking for any official communication or updates from the companies you\u2019re interested in. Additionally, connecting with peers who have gone through the same process can provide further insights.",
